## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="6b918-187">Gestire il <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource.ContextCreating> evento per fornire la propria <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> invece di un nuovo <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> creato.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6b918-187">Handle the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource.ContextCreating> event to supply your own <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> instead of having a new <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> created.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="6b918-188">Se il <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource.ContextCreating> evento non viene gestito o il gestore non fornisce un' <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext>, il <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource> viene creata una in base alla relativa configurazione.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6b918-188">If the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource.ContextCreating> event is not handled or the handler does not provide an <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext>, the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource> creates one according to its configuration.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="6b918-189">Quando un <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> viene fornito per il <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource.ContextCreating> evento, la stessa istanza viene assegnata per il `Context` proprietà dell'oggetto evento degli eventi successivi.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6b918-189">When an <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> is provided to the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSource.ContextCreating> event, the same instance is assigned to the `Context` property of the event object of successive events.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="6b918-190">Per altre informazioni, vedere [gestione del ciclo di vita contesto degli oggetti (EntityDataSource)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/67bc2486-112c-47c3-b23f-0297f7ac2160).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6b918-190">For more information, see [Object Context Life-Cycle Management (EntityDataSource)](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/67bc2486-112c-47c3-b23f-0297f7ac2160).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="6b918-191">Per ulteriori informazioni sul contesto dell'oggetto, vedere [la risoluzione di identità, la gestione dello stato e il rilevamento delle modifiche](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/3bd49311-0e72-4ea4-8355-38fe57036ba0).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6b918-191">For more information about the object context, see [Identity Resolution, State Management, and Change Tracking](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/3bd49311-0e72-4ea4-8355-38fe57036ba0).</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="6b918-192">Nell'esempio seguente viene illustrato come creare un <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> variabile del <xref:System.Web.UI.Page> dell'oggetto e assegnarlo al <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSourceContextCreatingEventArgs.Context%2A> proprietà del <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSourceContextCreatingEventArgs> oggetto.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="6b918-192">The following example shows how to create an <xref:System.Data.Objects.ObjectContext> variable of the <xref:System.Web.UI.Page> object and assign it to the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSourceContextCreatingEventArgs.Context%2A> property of the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.EntityDataSourceContextCreatingEventArgs> object.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
public partial class _Default : System.Web.UI.Page  
    {  
        AdventureWorksModel.AdventureWorksEntities objCtx =  
            new AdventureWorksModel.AdventureWorksEntities();  
  
        protected void EntityDataSource2_ContextCreating(object sender,   
            EntityDataSourceContextCreatingEventArgs e)  
        {  
            e.Context = objCtx;  
        }  
    }  
```
